{
  "stem": "71.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father would not accept it, because he said they're cooking on Saturday, and he would not be there on Saturdays because the factories were-- you know, people were working, they had to be given the soup on that Saturday.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father remained the way he was at night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was working at night.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You know, a [GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this gave him the time to sit.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was a very learned man, so he had the chance to learn the Torah at night, you know, when he was there.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And this was satisfactory to him, that-- Then we-- they started liquidating the ghetto and we escaped.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was-- there was a-- out-- almost out of the ghetto, but was still in the ghetto, they called it a-- what do they call it?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It will come back to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we went there, and we worked-- we worked on the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We brought my father there, my father was very sick.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He had diarrhea, and we brought him on a wheelbarrow in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was pitch black, and we brought him there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was with us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And every morning, we would go into the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were-- the Germans knew that they were liquidating the ghetto, and there were a lot of brushes and trees, and they were afraid that people will hide there.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So they took some men to cut out the trees, and the, the girls and the women were pulling it away and tying it up.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they gave us that time so much to eat that everybody got sick just from that much food, we could not digest any longer.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And this lasted-- and then one day they asked us to, to leave the cemetery.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
